 3 — Inside GDB: set breakpoint
gdb(gdb) break coder_routine

4 — Run the program
gdb(gdb) run

5 — NOW set scheduler-locking (after run, once threads exist)
gdb(gdb) set scheduler-locking on

6 — You're inside coder_routine — start stepping
gdb(gdb) step        # step into function calls
(gdb) next        # step over function calls
(gdb) print arg   # inspect the argument passed to the routine

7 — If you want to check other threads
gdb(gdb) info threads          # list all threads
(gdb) thread 2              # switch to thread #2

8 — Continue to next breakpoint or finish
gdb(gdb) continue